			  	<h3>Music</h3>
			  	<p id="adapleft">A Soundtrack for the Wheel of Time was released in 1999, featuring music inspired by the books. It was written, produced and performed by Robert Berry, and included 19 songs.<br>Various metal bands have taken inspiration from and written songs about the series, including Blind Guardian, Katana, Noble Beast and Shaidar Logoth, the last naming themselves after the cursed city in the series.<br>American Composer Seth Stewart produced a full-scale orchestral work entitled The Age of Legends based on the mythical era that takes place 100 generations before the main series.</p>
